  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Relief and Assistance to Conflict Affected Populations in Yemen</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The objective of this action is to provide coordinated and effective lifesaving humanitarian assistance to the most vulnerable populations affected by the crisis in Yemen, with a focus on Ma&#x2019;rib, Al Jawf, Al Bayda and Shabwa governorates (Ma&#x2019;rib Hub) and Abyan, Aden, Al Dhale, Lahj and Taizz governorates (Aden hub). Through this intervention, IOM is providing coordination, information management and emergency relief services that support vulnerable populations and humanitarian actors. This project is advancing humanitarian response in locations which require urgent service provision to acutely displaced populations, migrants, and Yemeni nationals. The locations targeted under this project are prioritized based on existing needs and service gaps, and IOM aims to further tailor response activities under this action to meetand prepare for emergency humanitarian needs. In addition, IOM is forging ahead with plans to integrate assistance and services in Marib and Aden hubs, in line with the current strategies of the humanitarian architecture in Yemen.</narrative>
  </description>
